THE BLACK MARE
Companion Warbeast — the cart's fifth soldier
"What looked like a rattle in her was only anticipation."

Bought from Hofgrir in Riften for 12,000 gold (Ch.24) — his prize destrier. BJORN
chose her, and chose her deliberately: he wanted a WARHORSE in the traces, not a
cart horse — an animal that fights for the road ahead, not one that merely walks it.
War-trained where Mable was only wagon-broke. Mable teaches her the routes, then
retires to Windstad Manor.

